Nikolaj commented on the journey that Jaime goes through with [[Brienne of Tarth]] in [[Season 3]]:

:&quot;I think Jaime is a very honorable man inside and I think he actually recognizes something of himself in Brienne, and it's kind of reawakened. But, I think the years spent in Kingâ&euro;&trade;s Landing, in that horrible place, has made him a very cynical human being and meeting someone who is almost naĂŻve, but also, just as you saidâ&euro;&rdquo;earnestâ&euro;&rdquo;is, even though he's not aware of itâ&euro;&rdquo;and heâ&euro;&trade;s not, [and if he did], he would never admit itâ&euro;&rdquo;but it does touch something inside of him.&quot;&lt;ref&gt;[http://wicnet.tumblr.com/post/48143112357/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-on-the-hand Game Of Thrones: Nikolaj Coster-Waldau On The Hand Jaime Was Dealt], Access Hollywood interview, April 16th, 2013&lt;/ref&gt;

Nikolaj also said what first went through his mind when he found out that Jaime would lose his right hand (in Season 3's &quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;):

:&quot;I thought that was likeâ&euro;&rdquo;just amazing. Itâ&euro;&trade;s such a horrible thing to happenâ&euro;Ś If he had to pick a limb to lose, this would be the last one, Iâ&euro;&trade;m sure. This is his sword hand, this is what defines him, this is the one thing that he is incredible atâ&euro;Ś I think he sees himself as a soldier and itâ&euro;&tilde;s very important for him and his identity to be the very best. And it has nothing to do with him being a Lannister and the family money and all the wealth and all that. Itâ&euro;&trade;s all about his skill and suddenly that one thing is gone and thatâ&euro;&trade;s just so interesting. For me as an actor, I know this is huge because, before this, he has this wonderful, annoying arrogance and wit and fearlessness with people and itâ&euro;&trade;s just interesting what will happen next. And of course, I know what will happen next, but I think that to have a guy who starts in this one extreme and you go to the other, you couldnâ&euro;&trade;t ask for more as an actor, really.&lt;ref&gt;[http://wicnet.tumblr.com/post/48143112357/game-of-thrones-nikolaj-coster-waldau-on-the-hand Game Of Thrones: Nikolaj Coster-Waldau On The Hand Jaime Was Dealt], Access Hollywood interview, April 16th, 2013&lt;/ref&gt;

